30/04/2003
WASHINGTON, United States -- The US State Department announced that Secretary of State Colin Powell will visit Tirana on Friday (2 May) to take part in the signing of the US-Adriatic Charter by Albania, Croatia and Macedonia. The event was scheduled originally to take place in Washington. The pact stipulates the co-ordination of NATO integration efforts among the countries, with an eye to strengthening regional stability. Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano described Powell's visit as confirmation of his country's political maturity. (AFP, USA Today, AP, Albanian Radio - 29/04/03)
